==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by [[w:Robert A. Heinlein|Robert A. Heinlein]] in his novel ''[[w:Stranger in a Strange Land|Stranger in a Strange Land]]'' (1961) in which the word is described as being from the word for “to [[drink]]” and, [[figuratively]], “to drink in all available aspects of reality”, “to become one with the [[observe]]d” in Heinlein’s fictitious [[Martian]] language.

